<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uncle sentenced in slaying of 4-year-old nephew  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NORFOLK, Va. (AP) - A Queens man was sentenced Thursday to 10
years in prison for his part in the murder of his 4-year-old nephew
on Christmas Eve 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Norfolk Circuit Judge Lydia C. Taylor spent five hours examining
evidence and listening to testimony before imposing the sentence on
Kyle K. Morton Sr., of Far Rockaway. She sentenced Morton to 20
years, with 10 of them suspended.
</P>
<P>
   The sentence exceeded the state's recommended guidelines calling
for a maximum of six years, five months. Prosecutor Linda F.
Connell said the departure was warranted.
</P>
<P>
   ''This was an aggravated case of felony murder that warranted a
complete departure from the guidelines,'' Connell said after the
sentencing. ''There was a period of psychological torture and
terror here from the man who had custody of the child.''
</P>
<P>
   Morton and his wife, Alison, 28, were arrested in March by New
York authorities. They were charged with murdering the boy, Kenze
Morton, who had been placed in their custody after a New York court
determined his mother provided inadequate care.
</P>
<P>
   Kenze was killed after ''acting up'' in a Norfolk apartment,
according to the Mortons' confessions. Alison Morton said she tied
him up and shoved him into a cupboard when she lost patience. Kyle
Morton stuffed a skull cap into Kenze's mouth, according to
investigators' notes, and Alison Morton later strangled the child
and went to bed.
</P>
<P>
   Two days later, the couple put Kenze into a weighted duffel bag
and threw his body into the Chesapeake Bay. The Mortons moved back
to New York soon after, and their crime wasn't discovered until
Kenze's jawbone washed up on the beach a year later.
</P>
<P>
   The Mortons both pleaded guilty to murder, and Alison Morton was
sentenced in March on a first-degree murder charge to 30 years in
prison.
</P>
<P>
   Defense attorney Gordon Zedd told Taylor on Thursday that Kyle
Morton denied placing a skull cap in Kenze's mouth before his
death. Kyle Morton also said that he told his wife to untie Kenze
before the couple fell asleep on Christmas Eve, Zedd said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
