<HEADLINE> 2 Plead in Brockovich Extortion  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   VENTURA, Calif. (AP) -- Three men have pleaded innocent to
charges that they tried to extort $310,000 from Erin Brockovich,
the outspoken legal secretary and environmental advocate.
</P>
<P>
   The case revolves around Brockovich's ex-husband Shawn Brown,
38, ex-boyfriend Jorg Halaby, 46, and lawyer John Reiner, 43, who
were arrested on charges of extortion.
</P>
<P>
   The complaint alleges the men threatened to tell tabloid media
that Brockovich and her boss, Ed Masry, had a sexual relationship
and that she was a bad mother -- neither of which was true,
according to officials.
</P>
<P>
   The men have steadfastly maintained they are innocent and
entered their pleas Thursday after many delays in the arraignment.
</P>
<P>
   Brockovich's work on a toxic waste case was the basis of a hit
movie starring Julia Roberts.
