<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-04 02:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Removed From Airplane Wheel Well  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A man found in the wheel well of an Air
France jet at Los Angeles International Airport late Thursday may
have been a stowaway who survived an overseas flight, authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
   ''We could see him secreted in the (main wheel) well,'' Fire
Department spokesman Jim Wells said. ''He was extricated from an
area that's not big enough to get comfortable in.''
</P>
<P>
   Wells said the man thrashed about as firefighters pulled him
out. He was taken to UCLA Medical Center with severe hypothermia
and was in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
   It wasn't clear how he could have survived a high-altitude
flight in the wheel well or if he might have been secreted in a
safer part of the plane during flight before climbing down after
landing.
</P>
<P>
   The Boeing 747 originated in Papeete, French Polynesia. A call
placed to Air France was answered by a recording.
</P>
<P>
