<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Open Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened higher. The Dow Jones
industrial average is up 4 points in today's early going. Advancing
issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 3-2 lead over
decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 52 points and the S&AMP;P 500
index is up 6 points.
</P>
<P>
   The market is taking today's unemployment report and running
with it.
</P>
<P>
   Just how far it will run remains to be seen.
</P>
<P>
   But, the July report showed a decline in payroll jobs of
108,000, when many analysts were looking for a small increase.
</P>
<P>
   So, the report certainly doesn't add to the pressure on the Fed
to raise interest rates at its meeting this month.
</P>
<P>
   And there's some hope on the Street that it will alleviate any
of the remaining pressure, and allow for another soft landing of
the economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
