<HEADLINE> 300 Blank US Passports Scattered  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 300 blank U.S. passports fell from a
government vehicle Friday and were scattered on the ground after
the box in which were they were contained was struck by a car, the
State Department said.
</P>
<P>
   The passports were being transported to the Passport Agency near
downtown Washington. The precise location of the mishap was not
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Many of the passports were recovered but others were picked up
by passersby, State Department spokesman Richard Boucher said.
</P>
<P>
   He said the State Department has electronically canceled all
passports involved in the incident.
</P>
<P>
   Boucher encouraged anyone in possession of blank passports to
turn them in to the State Department or to the Metropolitan Police
Department.
</P>
</TEXT>
